rel=3Dtag>web site=20
construction</A></DIV>
<P></P>
<P>After having the template tweaks to look at, I am making some more, =
leading=20
to <A =
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/default.htm.template.txt">version=20
0.03</A>:</P>
<UL>
  <LI>First, I make an unrelated addition to the RSS feeds, following =
the <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.labnol.org/internet/blogging/spam-websites-republish-b=
log-rss-feeds/4241/">advice=20
  of Amit Agarwal</A>.&nbsp; This is meant to deal with situations where =
the=20
  feed is mechanically republished by another site, preserving the =
origination=20
  of the feed item regardless.<BR>Each feed item will now have this=20
  footer:<BR><FONT size=3D2 face=3Dmonospace><STRONG>&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;a=20
  href=3D"</STRONG></FONT><A =
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/%22"><FONT size=3D2=20
  =
face=3Dmonospace><STRONG>http://nfoWorks.org/diary/"</STRONG></FONT></A><=
FONT=20
  size=3D2 face=3Dmonospace><STRONG> target=3D"_top" =
rel=3D"nofollow"&gt; nfoWorks:=20
  Pursuing Harmony&lt;/a&gt;</STRONG><FONT size=3D3 =
face=3Ddefault><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  </FONT></FONT>
  <LI>The entire sidebar is right-justified for more-consistent=20
  appearance.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>The title of the blog is centered.&nbsp; Eventually, there will be =
a logo=20
  in the upper-left corner and some links in the upper right.</LI></UL>
<P>I've started capturing pages that illustrate the state of the blog at =
each=20
template revision.&nbsp; These will be carried under the Blog Operations =

materials for reference.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Although I intentionally refrain from republishing the whole site, =
older=20
archive and post pages will be regenerated from time to time.&nbsp; Page =

regeneration, always using the then-latest template, is usually because =
comments=20
have been posted and sometimes because I provide additional information =
in an=20
older post (such as links to related recent material).</P>
